articles.description: Virginia suffered a surprising home loss to Virginia Tech on Saturday -- another sign that even the best teams have issues this season.
articles.headline: Virginia's loss to Virginia Tech reminder that every team has flaws

images.caption: Chris Clarke and Virginia Tech got a big win for their tourney chances while also bringing No. 2 Virginia back to Earth a bit.
images.name: Virginia Tech vs. Virginia (Virginia Tech Hokies forward Chris Clarke (15) shoots the ball ) [576x324]

articles.description: Justin Johnson had 25 points and a career-high seven rebounds, and Western Kentucky beat Florida International 83-76 on Saturday night.
articles.headline: Western Kentucky tops FIU 83-76

articles.description: Shannon Evans II scored 23 points, Tra Holder added 22 and Arizona State beat UCLA 88-79 on Saturday night for its first Pac-12 weekend sweep in three seasons under coach Bobby Hurley.
articles.headline: Arizona State beats UCLA 88-79 for rare Pac-12 sweep

articles.description: Jon Elmore tallied 22 points, seven rebounds and four assists and Ajdin Penava notched his 12th double-double of the season to guide Marshall to a 79-68 victory over Florida Atlantic on Saturday night.
articles.headline: Elmore, Penava lead Marshall past Florida Atlantic 79-68

articles.description: Ryan Kemrite and Elijah Cuffee had 15 points each and Liberty withstood Gardner-Webb down the stretch for a 77-65 win on Saturday night.
articles.headline: Liberty holds off Gardner-Webb 77-65

articles.description: Miye Oni scored 19 points with six rebounds and six assists and Yale defeated Cornell 74-65 on Saturday night.
articles.headline: Oni leads Yale to 74-65 win over Cornell
